    "text": "Strain measures how much cardiovascular load you accumulate across the whole day, on a 0-to-21 scale where the top end takes an all-out effort to reach. It only climbs, never falls, and the scale is logarithmic — each point gets progressively harder to earn. Today's strain of 8.6 sits well below your 7-day average strain of 12.3, which fits your log: the only session was a 38-minute easy spin. That's not a wasted day — lighter days like this are what let the harder ones land. If you're using strain to pace your week, the 7-day average is the number to watch rather than any single day.",
